Task-4(API's):-
1. The project is implemented as a React Movie Recommendation App that fetches movie data dynamically from the TVMaze API and displays it in a user-friendly interface.

2. API integration is implemented using the [fetch()] method with the TVMaze API link:

```js id="ikjlwm"
https://api.tvmaze.com/search/shows?q=${search}
```

The [${search}] value changes dynamically based on the user’s input.

3. React Hooks such as [useState] are used to manage application states like movie data, search text, loading status, popup details, errors, and dark mode theme.

4. The [useEffect()] hook is used to automatically call the API and load default movie data when the application starts.

5. Component reusability is achieved by separating the UI into reusable components such as [MovieCard] and [MoviePopup], making the code modular and easier to maintain.

6. The [MovieCard] component is reused multiple times using the [map()] function to display movie information dynamically for every API result.

7. Responsive design is implemented using CSS Grid, Flexbox, and responsive layouts so the application adapts properly to different screen sizes and devices.

8. UI quality is improved with modern styling features such as hover effects, popup modals, dark/light mode toggle, gradients, rounded corners, and smooth spacing for better user experience.

9. Clean coding practices are followed by organizing files into components, using meaningful variable names, applying conditional rendering, handling API errors properly, and keeping logic separated from styling.

10. Overall, the application demonstrates important React concepts including API integration, hooks, state management, reusable components, responsive UI development, conditional rendering, and modern frontend design practices.
